    "title": "The Body has a Mind...",
    "description": "&quot;I did not begin when I was born, nor when I was conceived. I have been growing, developing, through incalculable myriads of millenniums. All my previous selves have their voices, echoes, promptings in me. Oh, incalculable times again shall I be born.&quot; \n—Jack London, The Star Rover\n\n&quot;We can't solve problems by using the same kind of thinking we used when we created them.&quot;\n—Albert Einstein\n\nDiapause [dahy-uh-pawz]. \ndef. = a period of hormonally controlled quiescence, especially in immature insects.",
